---
import Sub2DirHeader from "/src/components/Sub2DirHeader.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<title>Dol</title>
		<link href="/dist/output.css" rel="stylesheet">
	</head>
	<style>
		@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono&display=swap');
	</style>
	<Sub2DirHeader bread="Dark Chocolate">
	</Sub2DirHeader>

	<div class="p-6 max-w-lg">
		<div class="text-xl font-bold">Dark Chocolate Sourdough</div>
		<div class="font-light text-neutral-500"><span class="text-xs italic">from</span> <a class="underline" href="https://www.nelsontheseagull.com/">Nelson the Seagull</a></div>
		<div class="py-4 space-y-2 flex flex-col">
			<span>This loaf came recommended from a friend.</span>			
			<div>I picked this up on a rainy Thursday morning before work.</div>
			<div>The loaf was still warm which made the walk home pleasant.</div>
			<div class="py-4 relative flex flex-row">
				<img class="h-72 w-72 object-cover rounded" src="/images/bread/nelson-chocolate2.jpg">
			</div>
			<div>
				<div class="pb-4">
					<div class="font-bold text-lg">Rating: 7/10 Toasters</div>
					<div class="p-2 bg-lime-800/50 border border-neutral-500 inline-flex rounded space-x-1">
						<img  class="h-6" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6 grayscale opacity-50" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6 grayscale opacity-50" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
						<img  class="h-6 grayscale opacity-50" src="/images/bread/toaster.png">
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div>This sourdough was particularly pretty. It was reminiscent of a dark rye but there were visible pockets of chocolate throughout.</div>
			<div class="">The a nutty bitterness that will appease dark chocolate enjoyers. I found the chocolate gave the crumb a nice moisture. 
			</div>
			<div class="">
				I enjoyed this bread most toasted with a light coating of warm peanut butter.
			</div>

		</div>
	</div>
</html>
